WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified display profile for ultra-high-resolution quantum dot
displays achieving 10,000 PPI and above. It defines the quantum dot
synthesis, electro-luminescent or photo-luminescent emission, sub-pixel
architecture at nanoscale, color primaries, luminance, and applications
in augmented reality (AR) and virtual reality (VR) headsets. This is
the canonical reference for GIOP ODTs targeting next-generation spatial
computing displays.

WHY IT EXISTS
AR/VR demands pixel densities far exceeding traditional displays to
eliminate the "screen door effect." Quantum dots enable this density
while maintaining wide color gamut. An ODT for these displays must
account for sub-pixel rendering at 10,000 PPI and the unique optical
stack of near-eye displays. This file provides the auditable model.

HOW IT WORKS
This file specifies:
  1. Quantum dot synthesis and emission principle.
  2. Pixel architecture at 10,000 PPI.
  3. Color primaries and luminance.
  4. Near-eye optical stack considerations.
  5. GIOP ODT configuration.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
